## üêõ Bug Report

In the application I am using sideMenu from react-native-navigation. In one of the screens I need to handle some swipe up / down gestures (handled with [react-native-swipe-gestures](https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-native-swipe-gestures)) to resize the bottom component. 

I noticed that using the property  `openGestureMode: 'entireScreen'` on sideMenu makes pulling the side menu easier than `'bezel'`mode and I would like to keep it. Unfortunately, when property is set to `'entireScreen'`, gesture recognizer works poorly. Many swipes up or down are missed compared to using 'bezel' mode.

I tried to change 'openGestureMode' onPressIn and onPressOut, to make it 'bezel' for the time of swipe gesture, but it did not work.

I created the function:
```
const handleChangeDrawerGestureMode = (openGestureMode) => {
  Navigation.mergeOptions('drawerComponentId', {
    sideMenu: { openGestureMode },
  });
};
```

and call with:
```
export const setDrawerGestureModeEntireScreen = () => handleChangeDrawerGestureMode('entireScreen');

export const setDrawerGestureModeBezel = () => handleChangeDrawerGestureMode('bezel');

```
but sideMenu do not change it's initial `openGestureMode`. I tried to change other properties like: `visible` and it works fine.

My navigation looks like:
```
export const pushDrawerNavigator = (dashboardComponentName, drawerComponentName) => {
  Navigation.setRoot({
    root: {
      sideMenu: {
        left: {
